thought, well, of course.

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:33.870
She had to eventually
get to the nuns, really.

00:05:33.870 --> 00:05:35.170
&gt;&gt; Alice McDermott: Honestly.

00:05:35.170 --> 00:05:36.470
Don't you think?

00:05:36.470 --> 00:05:37.770
&gt;&gt; Lynn Neary: Played a pretty
big role in the lives of anybody

00:05:37.770 --> 00:05:40.190
who grew up Catholic
at a certain time.

00:05:40.190 --> 00:05:41.490
&gt;&gt; Alice McDermott: Yes.

00:05:41.490 --> 00:05:45.730
Yeah, and I did have that sense
of especially this, New York,

00:05:45.730 --> 00:05:49.050
and I think probably any of
the major east coast cities.

00:05:49.050 --> 00:05:52.640
Even in my lifetime, I remember
walking through the streets

00:05:52.640 --> 00:05:56.340
of Brooklyn in the
late '50s or the '60s.

00:05:56.340 --> 00:05:58.580
Nuns were everywhere.

00:05:58.580 --> 00:06:00.980
And if you notice,
you never see them

00:06:00.980 --> 00:06:05.250
in contemporary film
