00:10:15.700 --> 00:10:18.310
&gt;&gt; Alice McDermott:
Probably both those things.

00:10:18.310 --> 00:10:23.790
I think among many little
pieces of advice, dismaying

00:10:23.790 --> 00:10:28.250
and confused advice that I
give to my writing students,

00:10:28.250 --> 00:10:33.590
is be careful your stories are not
too much about what they're about.

00:10:33.590 --> 00:10:37.580
I guess wonderful looks from
them when I say that, you know,

00:10:37.580 --> 00:10:40.300
like how the hell do I do that.

00:10:40.300 --> 00:10:46.110
But I think for me, while those
things are important and part

00:10:46.110 --> 00:10:50.500
of the life of these women,
of course, I didn't want them

00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:57.940
to overwhelm the more interesting
aspect which is the dailiness of,

00:10:57.940 --> 00:10:59.730
yes, there are love affairs, yes,

00:10:59.730 --> 00:11:02.740
there are suicides,
yes, there's depression.

00:11:02.740 --> 00:11:04.710
There's confusion.

00:11:04.710 --> 00:11:06.160
There's unrequited love.

00:11:06.160 --> 00:11:07.600
All those things are going on,

00:11:07.600 --> 00:11:11.120
the stuff that storytellers
make so much of.

00:11:11.120 --> 00:11:14.360
But underneath that, and this
is a novel that's very much

00:11:14.360 --> 00:11:16.500
about what goes on underground.

00:11:16.500 --> 00:11:17.800
&gt;&gt; Lynn Neary: Yeah.

00:11:17.800 --> 00:11:19.570
&gt;&gt; Alice McDermott: There
